Advocate Gerrie Nel says Senzo Meyiwa’s murder wasn’t a botched robbery, but an assassination. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The arrest of the alleged mastermind behind the killing of Senzo Meyiwa is expected soon, according to Advocate Gerrie Nel. READ: Senzo Meyiwa murder case postponed Nel was speaking to eNCA's Karima Brown on the Fix earlier. He is leading Afriforum's private prosecutions unit into the fatal shooting of the soccer star six years ago. On Tuesday, five suspects appeared at the Boksburg Magistrate's Court. They are accused of killing the late Orlando Pirates and Bafana Bafana goalkeeper. The men are expected to appear in court on 27 November. Watch the full interview above.